WEBVTT

01:02.209 --> 01:04.939
<i>All my life,
I always wanted to fly.</i>

01:06.045 --> 01:08.674
<i>I always wanted
to live like a hawk.</i>

01:10.084 --> 01:13.645
<i>I know you're not supposed
to be jealous of anything, but...</i>

01:13.721 --> 01:15.689
<i>to take flight,</i>

01:15.757 --> 01:19.090
<i>to soar above
everything and everyone,</i>

01:20.462 --> 01:22.555
<i>now that's living.</i>

01:41.184 --> 01:43.483
So, we'll burn
15 seconds off the clock,

01:43.554 --> 01:45.681
and we'll end this thing
our way in his house.

01:45.756 --> 01:48.817
We stack it up. I want Odin, Michael
and Billy to handle the ball.

01:48.893 --> 01:50.951
Hugo, you and Todd
set up the screens.

01:51.028 --> 01:54.021
At 13 seconds, we run
the Tulsa play for Odin. Give me that.

01:54.097 --> 01:57.261
Todd, you're in the stack
with Michael. Hugo? Hugo!

01:57.335 --> 02:00.702
You're at the right elbow. Billy, you're
at the low block on the weak side.

02:00.772 --> 02:04.174
And remember, lads.
Hugo and Todd are decoys.

02:04.243 --> 02:07.644
Decoys! I don't want to see either
one of those guys with the ball.

02:07.746 --> 02:11.147
At 13 seconds, we free up Odin
for the one on one, then clear!

02:11.217 --> 02:13.550
If it's not Odin, Michael.

02:13.620 --> 02:15.986
Put them in.
What time is it, team?

02:16.056 --> 02:17.045
Game time! Rah!

02:17.157 --> 02:18.385
All right, let's focus!

02:33.040 --> 02:34.200
Move, move!

02:36.077 --> 02:38.478
Good passes.
I want good passes!

02:40.015 --> 02:41.312
Keep it tight.

02:44.152 --> 02:45.449
Tight!

02:49.358 --> 02:51.486
Go, go, go!

02:51.561 --> 02:53.051
Take the ball!

02:56.099 --> 02:58.796
- Tulsa!
- Tulsa!

03:02.640 --> 03:04.232
Don't stop! Don't stop!

03:04.308 --> 03:05.741
Don't stop!

03:05.809 --> 03:09.472
Eight, seven, six, five,

03:09.473 --> 03:13.136
four, three, two, one!

03:14.119 --> 03:16.781
Yes! Yes! Yes!

04:24.762 --> 04:28.323
<i>Coach Duke Goulding!</i>

04:30.302 --> 04:32.793
<i>Thank you. Thank you.</i>

04:32.871 --> 04:34.771
Thank you very much.

04:34.840 --> 04:36.501
All right.

04:36.575 --> 04:38.475
Odin, would you
come down here, please?

04:38.543 --> 04:41.103
As you all know,
I am a man of few words.

04:41.179 --> 04:43.978
Except for when one of us
is late for practice, right, Pop?

04:44.050 --> 04:46.279
I'll pretend I don't know
who said that, Hugo.

04:46.351 --> 04:47.841
I'll get right to the point.

04:47.920 --> 04:50.787
By virtue of having won
our divisional championship,

04:50.857 --> 04:53.223
as well as having the best
record in the league,

04:53.292 --> 04:56.592
we will have home court advantage
in the State Championship,

04:56.697 --> 04:59.791
all the way up to, and
including, the semi-finals.

04:59.900 --> 05:04.634
And one reason for that is
this young man standing next to me.

05:04.706 --> 05:06.570
And I'll tell you
something else too-

05:08.041 --> 05:10.510
and I'm very proud
to say this publicly.

05:11.646 --> 05:14.274
I love him
like my own son.

05:19.020 --> 05:21.251
Not only is he a shoe-in

05:21.323 --> 05:23.951
for this year's USA Today
high school All American,

05:24.026 --> 05:26.757
but he is going
to lead this team

05:26.830 --> 05:29.197
to the 20th State Championship

05:29.447 --> 05:34.327
in the 115 year
history of this institution!

05:37.607 --> 05:39.235
You can stay on your feet,

05:39.310 --> 05:42.507
'cause at this time,
I am very proud to present

05:42.580 --> 05:44.810
this year's
unanimous choice

05:45.082 --> 05:48.501
for most valuable player
to Mr. Odin James.

05:49.130 --> 05:50.174
Congratulations.

05:56.128 --> 05:58.119
You know, at the beginning
of the season,

05:58.197 --> 06:00.358
we decided
to go all the way.

06:00.432 --> 06:02.798
And I did give it
all I had,

06:02.901 --> 06:07.168
but that wouldn't have meant nothing
if I didn't have a go-to guy.

06:07.240 --> 06:09.868
Big Mike,
come up here, man.

06:09.943 --> 06:14.107
Come on, now's not
the time to be shy. Come on.

06:15.748 --> 06:19.377
I told the coach
I wasn't accepting the MVP award

06:19.452 --> 06:22.980
unless the "man with the
hands" could share it with me.

06:23.057 --> 06:24.719
That's for you, baby.

06:25.694 --> 06:27.752
It's all you, baby.

07:24.523 --> 07:26.013
I don't understand.

07:26.092 --> 07:29.118
Are you going to get
Desi and I together?

07:29.195 --> 07:32.221
- She's with him.
- They're breaking up.

07:32.299 --> 07:35.757
When people are breaking up,
they don't grind.

07:35.835 --> 07:37.497
Those two
are definitely grinding.

07:37.572 --> 07:38.971
We're going to break them up.

07:40.741 --> 07:42.504
I thought
you were his friend.

07:42.611 --> 07:44.578
You hang out
with him all the time.

07:44.645 --> 07:46.511
And that's perfect,
'cause if we're going to do this,

07:46.581 --> 07:48.812
I've got to act like
I'm cool with him anyway.

07:48.884 --> 07:52.342
Look, you know
what a utility man is?

07:52.421 --> 07:53.649
A what?

07:54.723 --> 07:56.850
I'm considered
a utility man.

07:56.925 --> 08:00.555
I rebound, I can shoot.
I play guard, forward, power forward.

08:00.630 --> 08:02.894
You name the position,
I fucking play it.

08:04.901 --> 08:06.664
- What's your point?
- The point is,

08:06.736 --> 08:09.103
I'm the MVP
on this piece of shit team.

08:09.173 --> 08:12.573
I've been banging in the paint and
setting screens for the past four years,

08:12.643 --> 08:16.010
and he chooses Michael.
Fucking sophomore! No way!

08:19.116 --> 08:20.606
Look at this shit.

08:24.588 --> 08:28.582
- Roger, don't wuss out on me now.
- He'll boot me out of school.

08:28.661 --> 08:32.255
We are two blocks away from
the Roger Calhoon Senior Library.

08:32.330 --> 08:34.663
Your father is
this fucking institution.

08:34.734 --> 08:36.463
Do you want Desi or not?

08:48.615 --> 08:52.176
- Yes?
- Uh, hi. Dean Brable?

08:52.285 --> 08:53.843
Yes. Who is this?

08:53.955 --> 08:56.081
I don't know
how to tell you this, sir,

08:56.156 --> 08:58.785
but someone sort of stole
something from you.

08:58.860 --> 09:01.055
What are you talking about?

09:01.095 --> 09:02.392
Your daughter.

09:02.463 --> 09:05.432
What about my daughter?

09:05.501 --> 09:08.334
We're going to run them until
they drop dead or we drop dead!

09:08.404 --> 09:10.633
And that means
pressing on defense too.

09:10.705 --> 09:12.606
And by the way,
my friend, Hugo,

09:12.675 --> 09:14.506
your ass was dragging
in the fourth quarter.

09:14.576 --> 09:16.567
Either you get back
to your position on the traps,

09:16.645 --> 09:19.809
- or you give me some reason why.
- I'll be all right.

09:19.883 --> 09:22.579
You got to be better
than all right, son!

09:22.686 --> 09:24.779
Everybody
look at me, not him!

09:24.888 --> 09:27.652
This goes for you!
On your feet, gentlemen.

09:27.724 --> 09:30.022
Good afternoon, Dean.
You're welcome here.

09:30.093 --> 09:32.528
Good afternoon.

09:32.596 --> 09:35.394
And I have a witness who says
he forced himself on her.

09:35.465 --> 09:37.627
What? Who?

09:37.702 --> 09:42.470
Look, if Desi says that I did anything
even close to wrong to her,

09:42.541 --> 09:45.271
- I'll leave the goddamn school. OK?
- Take it easy, son.

09:45.343 --> 09:47.402
Bob, that's a very
serious allegation.

09:47.479 --> 09:50.642
- You say you have a witness?
- Come on, there's no witness.

09:50.716 --> 09:53.048
I would never do anything
like that. Ever.

09:53.118 --> 09:55.780
You're telling me you never
had any run-ins with the police?

09:55.888 --> 09:58.254
No, it means I didn't
force myself on Desi.

09:58.324 --> 10:00.849
That's not
what I just asked you.

10:00.960 --> 10:03.122
What are you trying to say?

10:03.197 --> 10:04.833
- You know what I'm saying.
- You're saying I'm not clean?

10:04.834 --> 10:06.359
Is that what you're sayin'?

10:06.432 --> 10:07.990
Cause I'm not
on that shit no more.

10:08.068 --> 10:09.467
Come on, coach,
you know this.

10:09.536 --> 10:12.061
I mean, test my ass.
Test me.

10:12.139 --> 10:14.198
This is fucked up.
This is fucked up.

10:14.274 --> 10:18.041
And a lot of the things I hear you say
about Desi are fucked up.

10:18.113 --> 10:20.171
- Bob.
- Don't underestimate me, son.

10:20.247 --> 10:22.876
Don't underestimate me
when it comes to my daughter.

10:22.951 --> 10:26.717
Hey, Bob! Please, please!
Back off! Now, come on. Please.

10:26.788 --> 10:28.120
If you were
so worried about me,

10:28.224 --> 10:30.616
how come this school
busted its ass to get me here?

10:30.617 --> 10:31.931
Because you were worth it!

10:32.962 --> 10:33.929
Yes?

10:33.996 --> 10:35.965
Come in, sweetheart.

10:36.065 --> 10:38.124
Please,
sit down over here.

10:38.200 --> 10:39.827
D, you've got to tell
these guys what's going on.

10:39.902 --> 10:43.394
- We know what's going on.
- We've got to be reasonable.

10:43.473 --> 10:44.371
Now, come on.

10:45.842 --> 10:47.139
Honey...

10:49.679 --> 10:52.477
we've never had
any secrets before, right?

10:52.549 --> 10:55.279
I just want you
to tell me the truth.

10:55.353 --> 10:57.651
Did Odin ever harm you,

10:57.722 --> 11:02.250
force you to do anything
that you didn't want to do?

11:02.360 --> 11:03.850
Anything at all?

11:06.298 --> 11:09.461
Odin and I have been
together for four months.

11:09.535 --> 11:13.403
"Together"?
What does that mean, "together"?

11:13.472 --> 11:15.064
Dad, that's none
of your business.

11:15.140 --> 11:17.371
I asked you a question.

11:18.477 --> 11:20.673
And I said
it's none of your business.

11:37.865 --> 11:40.698
Listen, Bob,
this is a family matter.

11:40.768 --> 11:43.431
Maybe we shouldn't be
discussing it here.

11:43.505 --> 11:46.338
I mean, he's a good kid.
Don't do this.

11:50.546 --> 11:51.911
Talk to him.

11:51.980 --> 11:53.949
Let's give him
a chance to talk.

11:54.016 --> 11:55.608
Outside.

12:01.859 --> 12:07.593
Sir, I just want to tell you that
you've got a great daughter there.

12:08.999 --> 12:11.969
And I really,
really care about her.

12:12.036 --> 12:17.167
You've got to understand
that what we have is beautiful.

12:19.879 --> 12:22.745
No. She deceived me.

12:24.149 --> 12:26.673
What makes you think
she won't do the same to you?

12:31.824 --> 12:35.283
If you ever lie on me again, I'll fuck
your punk ass up a lot worse than this.

12:35.362 --> 12:37.922
You understand me, Rog? Huh?

12:42.769 --> 12:44.236
See you at dinner.

13:14.637 --> 13:17.765
You're going to keep doing
this shit all year, yo?

13:17.874 --> 13:20.207
You tell me, man.
You're the pharmacist.

13:22.145 --> 13:26.674
You know, some of these drugs I sell
will guarantee to have you twisted up.

13:26.750 --> 13:30.550
This steroid,
50-50 chance.

13:30.621 --> 13:32.487
I put three inches
on my vertical this month.

13:32.556 --> 13:35.082
I took half a second
off my 40, bro'.

13:36.260 --> 13:37.421
It's doing the job.

13:37.495 --> 13:41.022
When you start playing for North
Carolina, don't forget about me.

13:41.099 --> 13:42.965
Shoot the nigger
some tickets.

13:43.035 --> 13:45.025
I'm talking about court side.

13:55.548 --> 13:58.108
We're going to cycle you
to something else next week.

13:58.184 --> 13:59.948
You've been drinking
enough water?

14:00.020 --> 14:02.250
By the gallon, man.

14:02.322 --> 14:06.349
I'm surprised it doesn't come out
these holes you keep sticking in me.

14:06.427 --> 14:09.486
<i>I know you're all into
this basketball stuff,</i>

14:09.563 --> 14:12.089
<i>but if it don't work,
don't trip.</i>

14:12.166 --> 14:15.567
I'm saying cause there's some things
in life we weren't meant to have.

14:15.637 --> 14:18.663
I mean, don't go out there making
yourself all crazy and shit.

14:18.740 --> 14:22.574
How can I go crazy when I've got
you selling me dream in a bottle, man?

14:26.081 --> 14:27.549
<i>So, have you talked
to him about it?</i>

14:27.650 --> 14:29.514
There's nothing to talk about.

14:29.585 --> 14:31.577
I do everything for him,

14:31.687 --> 14:34.417
<i>but he's been acting
completely weird lately.</i>

14:34.490 --> 14:36.516
<i>Lately? Try always.</i>

14:36.593 --> 14:38.562
<i>Sorry.</i>

14:38.628 --> 14:40.324
What's the deal?

14:40.397 --> 14:43.059
Everyone at school
likes Hugo, except you.

14:43.133 --> 14:44.623
<i>Nobody doesn't like him.</i>

14:44.702 --> 14:47.227
I don't trust anyone who doesn't
have at least one enemy.

14:47.304 --> 14:49.101
<i>Well, I guess he does.</i>

14:49.173 --> 14:50.573
<i>I didn't think
you were going to make it.</i>

14:50.641 --> 14:52.166
Oh, come on now.

14:53.378 --> 14:55.368
You know I can't beat
Magnolia tomorrow

14:55.480 --> 14:57.607
without seeing
my good luck charm first.

14:57.716 --> 15:00.116
- What's up, Em?
- Hey.

15:00.185 --> 15:02.153
Hey, I've got
something for you.

15:12.131 --> 15:13.689
It's over 100 years old.

15:13.766 --> 15:16.327
It's over your price
range is what it is.

15:16.403 --> 15:20.567
It was my great-grandmother's and
it's always been in my family.

15:20.641 --> 15:23.542
It's supposed
to stay that way, but...

15:23.610 --> 15:26.010
I feel like
we're already family.

15:27.081 --> 15:29.107
Yo, Em, don't think
I forgot you.

15:29.217 --> 15:31.048
I got the new Harlem's
Finest for you, baby.

15:31.152 --> 15:32.983
Enjoy that, all right?

15:53.009 --> 15:55.034
Come on, Emily's here.

15:55.111 --> 15:58.047
I know.
We're not going to do anything.

15:58.115 --> 16:01.312
I just like feeling
your skin next to mine, okay?

16:01.418 --> 16:03.011
Come on.

16:13.498 --> 16:18.903
My father's a smart man. But he's
never actually been through anything.

16:21.941 --> 16:26.070
He acts like he's in control all
the time, but really he's just scared.

16:26.145 --> 16:28.205
You never seem scared to me.

16:28.281 --> 16:31.079
Are you asking me how
I got that scar on my back?

16:32.152 --> 16:34.177
You do have
the best stories.

16:36.356 --> 16:39.326
I was a C-section baby
and they cut too far.

16:39.426 --> 16:42.953
My mom couldn't afford
a good doctor.

16:44.565 --> 16:45.998
Are you serious?

16:46.067 --> 16:48.160
I fell off my skateboard.

16:49.537 --> 16:51.472
Are you crazy?
I get scared all the time.

16:51.539 --> 16:53.064
- You do not.
- Yes, I do.

16:53.141 --> 16:54.073
When?

16:55.277 --> 16:57.075
When?

16:57.145 --> 16:58.772
Okay.

16:58.847 --> 17:01.544
The first time
I tried to talk to you,

17:01.617 --> 17:04.210
I thought I was going
to faint, or something.

17:04.287 --> 17:05.481
That's not true.

17:05.555 --> 17:08.286
The second sentence out of your mouth
was, "Do you still have a boyfriend?"

17:08.391 --> 17:10.052
I said I was scared.

17:10.160 --> 17:12.458
I never said I couldn't
handle the pressure.

17:12.529 --> 17:15.225
You know I've got
them player skills.

17:15.299 --> 17:17.733
Oh, Ladies and Gentlemen
he's getting a little cocky.

17:17.801 --> 17:20.827
Don't say "Iittle" and "cocky" in
the same sentence when it comes to me.

17:20.905 --> 17:23.339
Especially
when you know the deal.

17:23.407 --> 17:24.875
Shut up!

17:26.544 --> 17:29.911
No, but you really
think I'm too cocky?

17:29.981 --> 17:32.074
No, it's okay.
You should be.

17:32.150 --> 17:35.244
- You pulled me, didn't you?
- Yes, I did.

17:35.320 --> 17:37.515
Yes, indeed, I did.

17:38.856 --> 17:40.449
I don't know how,
but you did it.

17:40.526 --> 17:42.187
What do you mean,
you don't know how?

17:42.295 --> 17:44.558
I pulled you 'cause
I'm that kind of nigger.

17:45.965 --> 17:49.402
Uh-oh. Don't be
acting like that.

17:49.469 --> 17:51.835
See, I can say "nigger"
cause I am a nigger.

17:51.905 --> 17:54.669
You can't 'cause you ain't.
Don't be jealous.

17:54.741 --> 17:57.904
And why can't I say it?
My people invented the word.

17:57.978 --> 17:59.445
You can't even think it.

17:59.512 --> 18:01.105
You're the one
who started it.

18:01.182 --> 18:03.377
You said I was so fine
you'd let me dress you up

18:03.451 --> 18:05.977
and play Black Buck
Got Loose in the Big House.

18:06.054 --> 18:07.520
Don't go repeating
that, all right?

18:07.589 --> 18:09.818
If another Black person
knew I said that,

18:09.890 --> 18:11.825
I could get my
suffering-Negro- league card revoked.

18:16.798 --> 18:21.065
Then you'd better watch out, because
I've got some dirt on you, player.

18:21.137 --> 18:23.195
Got some dirt on me, huh?

18:23.306 --> 18:24.898
You better not
let that leak.

18:26.509 --> 18:30.741
<i>And now, your year 2000...</i>

18:30.813 --> 18:36.047
<i>low country preparatory
league champion,</i>

18:36.120 --> 18:42.117
<i>Palmetto Grove Hawks!</i>

20:01.579 --> 20:02.705
Push! Push!

20:24.371 --> 20:26.235
Shit.

20:27.808 --> 20:29.400
<i>Injured on the floor.</i>

20:29.510 --> 20:33.446
<i>Palmetto Grove's
number four, Odin James.</i>

20:42.290 --> 20:44.622
- Is he okay?
- They're doing a CAT scan right now,

20:44.692 --> 20:47.388
so we'll see.
Don't worry.

20:47.462 --> 20:49.157
Edmund, did you bring
the insurance card?

20:49.230 --> 20:50.755
- I've got the card.
- So we're covered?

20:53.536 --> 20:56.596
Mickey gets more kisses
from my girl than I do.

20:56.672 --> 20:59.197
Could you stop being
a sarcastic asshole just once?

20:59.275 --> 21:03.006
I was joking,
all right? Relax.

21:03.113 --> 21:05.843
What's the deal?
I'm gone for a couple of hours

21:05.949 --> 21:07.473
and you're already
taking my girl, Big Mike?

21:09.920 --> 21:12.650
- What's up, dude?
- You get right home and get some rest.

21:12.722 --> 21:14.987
I will, man.
What's up, baby?

21:18.062 --> 21:19.654
I was worried about you.

21:19.730 --> 21:21.561
You were the one
who got hurt, stupid.

21:21.632 --> 21:23.601
No, you don't understand.

21:23.668 --> 21:25.761
I was worried that
if I hurt myself,

21:25.838 --> 21:28.271
who was going to take care
of you over there at Duke?

21:28.340 --> 21:29.864
Oh, right, right.

21:29.942 --> 21:31.910
You're still going to play
"Big House" with me, though, right?

21:31.978 --> 21:34.446
Hey, stop it with that.

21:34.514 --> 21:37.005
Then you better
stop getting hurt.

21:37.115 --> 21:40.016
- I love you.
- I love you too.

21:40.086 --> 21:43.055
You kids need to get back
to the dorms. Let's go, Hugo.

21:43.122 --> 21:45.181
I'm going to give
a shout at the boys, all right?

21:45.259 --> 21:46.953
- Mike.
- Hey, man.

21:47.026 --> 21:49.996
- We did our thing today, bro'.
- Yeah, we did good.

21:51.332 --> 21:53.300
What's up, Em?
How are you doing?

21:53.367 --> 21:54.925
Hugo.

21:55.003 --> 21:57.527
Thought we lost you
there for a second, bro.

21:57.605 --> 22:00.268
I ain't going nowhere.
But did we take it to them or what?

22:00.342 --> 22:03.106
You took it to them by yourself.
You know that, player.

22:03.178 --> 22:05.043
You're coming to
that party off campus?

22:05.114 --> 22:07.513
Yeah, I need to get a ride
with my dad, though.

22:07.582 --> 22:09.574
All right, man.
Don't take too long.

22:09.684 --> 22:10.981
Later, Hugo.

22:13.588 --> 22:15.853
Come on, don't worry.
He'll get there.

22:17.326 --> 22:19.420
Yeah, Roger.

